draw(((0.6,-0.6)--(6,-0.6)),EndArrow);
draw(((-6,0)--(0,6)));
draw(((0,6)--(6,0)));
draw(((0,0)--(0,6)),dashed);
label("$6$",(0,2.5),E);
[/asy] In this case, the height is $6\text{ cm}$, so the area of the triangle is $$\frac 12\cdot 12\cdot 6 = \boxed{36}\text{ square centimeters}.$$

