Since $\tan{M}=\frac{5}{4}$, we have $\dfrac{NO}{OM} = \dfrac{5}{4}$, so  $$NO = \frac{5}{4}OM = \frac{5}{4}\cdot 8 = 10.$$Then, from the Pythagorean Theorem, we have \begin{align*}
MN&=\sqrt{NO^2+OM^2}\\
&=\sqrt{10^2+8^2}=\sqrt{164}=\boxed{2\sqrt{41}}.\end{align*}

